fields.physical_description:
The parts for the skeleton are of moulded plastic.  They are boxed in a card box with expanded polystyrene trays and it is necessary to keep the two plastics apart.  When the box is used for storage please totally cover each tray and heat seal them before placing the parts into their spaces.

1.  box lid, card printed in colours to show the title in four languages (Spanish, English, French and Arabic), the maker's name and pictures of the made up model and various parts.
2.  box base, plain white card
3,4.  trays which are cut out and shaped to house the various parts, expanded polystyrene *PLEASE SEE NOTE ABOVE.
5.  booklet, printed in colours and in three languages (English, French and Arabic) to show and list all the parts of the body with some explanatory text.  8in x 5 5/8in
6.  sheet of red cellophane to be used as a filter.  It blocks out the red lettering and may be used to test the person using the book and model
7.  poster printed in colours to show pictures of part of the skeleton and internal organs together with one of the complete figure.
8.  stand
9.  outer skin, front of the figure
10.  outer skin, back of the figure
11.  face, with eye sockets, nose and teeth

Catalogue entry - NB6188/7 COMPLETE ANATOMY 1:5 SCALE

An accurate skeleton which can then be filled with modesl of the body's internal organs - heart, lungs, liver, stomach etc.  The completed body can them be held in the transparent body shell for easy viewing.  All parts are accurately scaled and offer a sound introduction to the understanding of the body's make-up.  Complete with stand and comprehensive guide.

Price: £46.20 + VAT
